data.content:
Here's what needs to change for each item in .NET 10:

---

### 1. `WebHostBuilder` → `WebApplication.CreateBuilder()`
`WebHostBuilder` is marked `[Obsolete]` in .NET 10. Migrate to the minimal hosting model:

```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
var host = new WebHostBuilder()
    .UseStartup<Startup>()
    .Build();

// After (.NET 10)
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
// move ConfigureServices → builder.Services
// move Configure → app.UseXxx() / app.MapXxx()
var app = builder.Build();
```

---

### 2. `.WithOpenApi()` removed
The per-endpoint `.WithOpenApi()` extension is removed. Use document-level OpenAPI generation instead:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenApi();
// ...
app.MapOpenApi();
```

To customize individual endpoint metadata, use document/operation transformers or endpoint metadata (e.g., `[EndpointSummary]`, `[EndpointDescription]`).

---

### 3. `<IncludeOpenAPIAnalyzers>` renamed
The MSBuild property is renamed:

```xml
<!-- Before -->
<IncludeOpenAPIAnalyzers>true</IncludeOpenAPIAnalyzers>

<!-- After -->
<EnableOpenApiAnalyzers>true</EnableOpenApiAnalyzers>
```

---

### 4. `Microsoft.Extensions.ApiDescription.Client` (NSwag codegen)
The MSBuild target `GetOpenApiReference` was renamed to `GenerateOpenApiCode`. If you have custom targets that hook into the code-gen pipeline, update the target name references. The `OpenApiReference` item group still works, but review your NSwag version for .NET 10 TFM compatibility.

---

### 5. `IActionContextAccessor` as singleton → **scoped**
`IActionContextAccessor` is now enforced as **scoped** in .NET 10. Registering it as a singleton will throw at startup:

```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IActionContextAccessor, ActionContextAccessor>();

// After (.NET 10)
builder.Services.AddHttpContextAccessor(); // if needed
builder.Services.AddScoped<IActionContextAccessor, ActionContextAccessor>();
// — or simply —
builder.Services.AddControllers(); // registers it automatically with correct lifetime
```

---

### 6. `IPNetwork` type replaced
`Microsoft.AspNetCore.HttpOverrides.IPNetwork` is removed. Use the BCL type `System.Net.IPNetwork` (available since .NET 8):

```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.HttpOverrides;
options.KnownNetworks.Add(new IPNetwork(IPAddress.Parse("10.0.0.0"), 8));

// After (.NET 10)
using System.Net;
options.KnownNetworks.Add(new IPNetwork(IPAddress.Parse("10.0.0.0"), 8));
```

The constructor signature is the same — only the `using` changes. The `ForwardedHeadersOptions.KnownNetworks` collection now expects `System.Net.IPNetwork`.

---

### 7. `AddRazorRuntimeCompilation()` removed
The `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Razor.RuntimeCompilation` package is no longer published for .NET 10. Use **Hot Reload** instead:

```bash
dotnet watch
```

Remove the package reference and any `AddRazorRuntimeCompilation()` calls. Hot Reload covers the same dev-time Razor editing scenario without the runtime compilation overhead.

---

### 8. 401 redirect → proper 401 status for APIs
.NET 10 changes the default cookie authentication behavior for API endpoints. Instead of redirecting to a login page on 401/403, API endpoints now receive the raw status codes. If you were working around this with custom logic, you can simplify:

```csharp
// Before (.NET 9) — manual workaround
builder.Services.ConfigureApplicationCookie(options =>
{
    options.Events.OnRedirectToLogin = ctx =>
    {
        ctx.Response.StatusCode = 401;
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    };
});

// After (.NET 10) — automatic for endpoints with [ApiController]
// or endpoints that Accept: application/json.
// Remove the workaround; the framework handles it.
```

If you need the old redirect behavior for specific paths, configure `CookieAuthenticationOptions.ForwardDefaultSelector` or set `options.Events.OnRedirectToLogin` explicitly.

---

### Summary checklist

| Area | Action |
|---|---|
| Hosting model | Replace `WebHostBuilder` with `WebApplication.CreateBuilder()` |
| OpenAPI endpoints | Drop `.WithOpenApi()`, use `AddOpenApi()` + `MapOpenApi()` |
| OpenAPI analyzers | Rename MSBuild prop to `EnableOpenApiAnalyzers` |
| NSwag codegen | Update target references (`GenerateOpenApiCode`) |
| `IActionContextAccessor` | Change to scoped registration |
| `IPNetwork` | Switch `using` to `System.Net` |
| Razor runtime compilation | Remove package; use `dotnet watch` |
| 401 redirects | Remove workaround; framework returns 401 for APIs |
